description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Service Team Manager, Community Learning Disabilities Health Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic professional to lead our commissioned Community Learning Disabilities Health Team in Brent. The post holder will have an integral role in service development, provide effective day to day management of the team, ensuring that performance standards of the team are met. They will operationally manage a health service of therapists, nurses, psychologists and work alongside psychiatrists and other disciplines to ensure that a seamless safe and comprehensive service is provided. This team will be based at the Kingswood Centre, working in close collaboration with Local Authority colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must have: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Professional Registration as a Registered Learning Disabilities or Mental Health Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent leadership and motivational skills.&lt;br /&gt;Robust performance management skills &lt;br /&gt;Experience of multi agency partnership working &lt;br /&gt;Thorough understanding of current drivers in learning disabilities &lt;br /&gt;Experience of undertaking appraisals and supervisions within teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity for an experienced and confident practitioner. The post holder will be able to provide leadership and expertise to a new team of clinicians and admin staff to ensure people with learning disabilities are supported to live as valued members of society, by providing and arranging specialist healthcare and supporting access to generic health services where possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date:23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Josephine Carroll&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Head of Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Josephine.carroll@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0208 238 0900&lt;/p&gt;
